         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">24/12/86 ¶  ¶ It is true I have not yet compared the short-haired  ¶ Lhotzkya ¶  from Kang. Island ¶  with original specimens in my museum from the Grampians, ¶  dear Mr Tepper, but I do not doubt tha...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">86.12.24</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Otto Tepper</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">RB MSS M198, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne </p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>MS annotation by Tepper: 'Reply Jan 87'. Letter not found.</p>
               </note>24/12/86</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Zwar habe ich die kurzhaarige Lhotzkya von der Käng. Insel noch nicht mit Original-Exemplaren von den Grampians in meinem Museum verglichen, lieber Herr Tepper, doch zweifle ich nicht, dass es eine kleine Form von L. genethylloides ist</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Mir ist Prof. Tate's Liste eben nicht zur Hande, veilleicht ist auch diese Lhotzkya bereits darin angeführt. In den Grampians kommt ein Bastard zwischen dieser Pfl. u <name key="Calycothrix%20tetragona">Calycothrix tetragona</name> vor.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Mit besten Wünschen zum neues Jahr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               </seg>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">24/12/86</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is true I have not yet compared the short-haired <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Lhotzkya</seg> from Kang. Island<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Kangaroo Island, SA.</p>
               </note> with original specimens in my museum from the Grampians,<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Vic.</p>
               </note> dear Mr Tepper, but I do not doubt that it is a small form of <seg style="font-style: italic; ">L. genethylloides</seg>.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M later described this as a new species, <seg style="font-style: italic; ">L. smeatoniana</seg> (B87.01.02, p. 5); see M to O. Tepper, 31 December 1886.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Professor Tate's list is not just at hand, perhaps this <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Lhotzkya</seg> is also already cited in it. In the Grampians a hybrid between this plant and <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Calycothrix%20tetragona">Calycothrix tetragona</name>
               </seg> occurs.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>With best wishes for the New Year</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Calycothrix%20tetragona">Calycothrix tetragona</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Lhotzkya%20genethylloides">Lhotzkya genethylloides</name>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
